{"TopicId":91366,"ForumId":55,"TopicTitle":"Make One of the Moons of Jool have Its Own Moon","CreatedByName":"arkie87","CreatedById":103434,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-11-27T05:22:54Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"arkie87","CreatedById":103434,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-11-27T05:22:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EIs it possible for a large moon of a large (gas) planet to have its own moon, or would the gravity from the large (gas) planet steal it inevitably over time? \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EEither way, should one of these be put into KSP?\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222014-11-27T06:30:53Z\u0022 title=\u002211/27/2014 06:30  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00229 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 27, 2014\u003C/time\u003E by arkie87\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rakaydos","CreatedById":101988,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-11-27T05:28:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E#Save the Magic Boulder\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Steambirds","CreatedById":62753,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-11-27T05:39:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EIt\u0027d be neat if Laythe had its own tiny Mun analogue.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"arkie87","CreatedById":103434,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-11-27T05:45:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Rakaydos\u0022 data-cite=\u0022Rakaydos\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E#Save the Magic Boulder\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EI see.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EBut a moon with a SOI would be cool too...\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"arkie87","CreatedById":103434,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-11-27T05:50:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Steambirds\u0022 data-cite=\u0022Steambirds\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003EIt\u0027d be neat if Laythe had its own tiny Mun analogue.\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAnd if a minmus analogue orbited the mun analogue \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue2.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:sticktongue:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-11-27T06:56:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/threads/68619-0-25-Plugin-WIP-KittopiaTech-Ingame-Terraforming-Tools-V0-181\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/threads/68619-0-25-Plugin-WIP-KittopiaTech-Ingame-Terraforming-Tools-V0-181\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/threads/91363-WIP-Planet-Randomizer-0-2-4-%282014-09-21%29\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/threads/91363-WIP-Planet-Randomizer-0-2-4-%282014-09-21%29\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"vexx32","CreatedById":12283,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-11-27T07:10:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EExcept under very unusual circumstances, the gravity of the parent planet would almost always end up either completely destabilising the sub-moon\u0027s orbit, or it might even end up tearing the sub-moon apart completely, depending on the distance from the parent planet.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"arkie87","CreatedById":103434,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-11-27T14:08:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022vexx32\u0022 data-cite=\u0022vexx32\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003EExcept under very unusual circumstances, the gravity of the parent planet would almost always end up either completely destabilising the sub-moon\u0027s orbit, or it might even end up tearing the sub-moon apart completely, depending on the distance from the parent planet.\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EYes, so i figure, for it to be stable, it would have to be near the SOI boundary or at least in very high orbit around the planet, and the parent moon would have to be relatively large compared to the sub moon\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Whirligig Girl","CreatedById":36077,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-11-27T14:17:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EI think Tylo would have the biggest SOI of the Joolean moons but also the biggest Roche limit.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"rtxoff","CreatedById":107622,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-11-27T14:19:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EAs far as i know the planets/moons in KSP are hard coded. It should be no problem to put even a larger moon into the game even if it wouldn\u0027t work that way in real life.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"arkie87","CreatedById":103434,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-11-27T14:22:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022 data-cite=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/threads/68619-0-25-Plugin-WIP-KittopiaTech-Ingame-Terraforming-Tools-V0-181\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/threads/68619-0-25-Plugin-WIP-KittopiaTech-Ingame-Terraforming-Tools-V0-181\u003C/a\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/threads/91363-WIP-Planet-Randomizer-0-2-4-%282014-09-21%29\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/threads/91363-WIP-Planet-Randomizer-0-2-4-%282014-09-21%29\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003ECan this do what I am suggesting? It doesnt seem like it can put a moon in the SOI of another moon and that moon still have its own SOI?\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Whirligig Girl","CreatedById":36077,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-11-27T15:05:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022gpisic\u0022 data-cite=\u0022gpisic\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003EAs far as i know the planets/moons in KSP are hard coded. It should be no problem to put even a larger moon into the game even if it wouldn\u0027t work that way in real life.\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EYes but all the orbits (not accounting for barycentric behaviors) are designed to work IRL. Indeed, in an N-body physics simulation, all of the planets and moons are stable (except for the Joolean moons; Vall and Pol eventually get ejected). If you \u003Cem\u003Edo\u003C/em\u003E account for the model\u0027s barycenters, then everything works out, Vall and Pol are stable.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022 contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Ciframe width=\u0022480\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/qKp1M4T6z24?feature=oembed\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022 contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Ciframe width=\u0022459\u0022 height=\u0022344\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/8DF4LgYl5DM?feature=oembed\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003Cp\u003EVideos by \u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/user/mattasmack/videos\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EMatt Roesle\u003C/a\u003E.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAlso, just for fun, Alternis Kerbol and Urania Planet Pack N-Body sim.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022 contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Ciframe width=\u0022480\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/aGvYWqj7dfk?feature=oembed\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022 contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Ciframe width=\u0022459\u0022 height=\u0022344\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/Ro7adH0a8z4?feature=oembed\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cem\u003EChaos!\u003C/em\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}